# Copy this file to .dev.vars and fill in your own values for local
# development (`.dev.vars` is gitignored — never commit real secrets).
#
# In production, set secrets with `wrangler secret put <NAME>` instead.

# LLM mode (see README "LLM modes" for details). ClipFeed already works with
# NEITHER of the below set — it falls back to the free Workers AI default via
# the native AI binding, no config needed. Set one of these to upgrade to a
# real Claude model.

# --- AI Gateway mode (recommended upgrade): route calls through Cloudflare ---
# --- AI Gateway. Uncomment both and leave ANTHROPIC_API_KEY empty, unless ---
# --- you want a per-request BYOK passthrough alongside the gateway. ---
# AI_GATEWAY_URL=https://gateway.ai.cloudflare.com/v1/<account_id>/<gateway_id>/anthropic
# CF_AIG_TOKEN=

# --- Direct mode: call api.anthropic.com straight. ---
# Get a key at https://console.anthropic.com/
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Optional local overrides of the [vars] defaults in wrangler.toml.
# SUMMARY_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
# WORKERS_AI_MODEL=@cf/meta/llama-3.3-70b-instruct-fp8-fast
# DAILY_SUMMARY_LIMIT=80
# PENDING_TIMEOUT_MIN=10

# How much summary you want to read: target TOTAL body length in characters
# (all paragraphs, per language) — the prompt and validation both derive
# their numbers from this one setting. Valid range 400-4000; anything
# missing/invalid/out of range falls back to 800. See README "Summary
# length".
# SUMMARY_BODY_TARGET_CHARS=800

# Faithfulness check (see README "Faithfulness check"): a SEPARATE judge
# pass, always Workers AI Llama regardless of which model wrote the
# summary, that verifies a summary against its source before the article
# is marked ready. FAITHFULNESS_CHECK defaults to "true" (only the literal
# "false" disables it — no judge call, no faithfulness columns written,
# pipeline behaves exactly as before this feature). FAITHFULNESS_ENFORCE
# defaults to "false" (soft/signal-only: a 'fail' verdict is stored and
# shown as a badge but never blocks the article) — only the literal "true"
# turns on the enforce path (one resummarize retry, then a permanent
# discard if that retry still fails the judge). FAITHFULNESS_JUDGE_MODEL
# is the Workers AI model id to judge with; same default as
# WORKERS_AI_MODEL above but a separate setting, since an owner running
# Claude via gateway/direct for summarization still wants a specific Llama
# judge model.
# FAITHFULNESS_CHECK=true
# FAITHFULNESS_ENFORCE=false
# FAITHFULNESS_JUDGE_MODEL=@cf/meta/llama-3.3-70b-instruct-fp8-fast

# Daily scraping agent (see README "Daily scraping agent"; sources live in
# packages/api/sources.json, not here). INTEREST_TOPICS steers the ranking
# call's taste — free text, edit to match what you actually want surfaced.
# AGENT_HOUR_UTC is a UTC hour (0-23); clearing it to an empty string
# disables the job. AGENT_DAILY_PICKS is how many candidates the agent
# saves per run — valid range 1-20, anything missing/invalid falls back to
# 10.
# INTEREST_TOPICS=AI/LLMs and their engineering; computer hardware — CPUs, GPUs, NVIDIA/Intel/AMD, chips; Linux — kernel, distributions, open source ecosystem; software development and programming languages; Cloudflare and edge computing; security; notable science/tech news
# AGENT_HOUR_UTC=5
# AGENT_DAILY_PICKS=10

# Cloudflare Access protection (see README "Protecting your instance").
# Optional — auth middleware only activates once BOTH are set. Without them
# a deployed instance is PUBLIC. Set via `wrangler secret put` in production;
# fine to set here for local testing against a real Access app.
# ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN=your-team.cloudflareaccess.com
# ACCESS_AUD=

# Cloudflare Turnstile bot protection (see README "Bot protection
# (Turnstile)"). Optional — only activates once BOTH are set. Requests
# carrying a verified Access identity bypass Turnstile entirely, so a
# request from the Chrome extension or a bot using an Access service token
# never sees a widget. TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY is public (safe in [vars] too);
# TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY must be a real secret (`wrangler secret put` in
# production).
#
# For local dev, Cloudflare publishes test keys that always pass/fail —
# no real Turnstile widget/dashboard setup needed to exercise the code path:
#   always passes:  site 1x00000000000000000000AA  secret 1x0000000000000000000000000000000AA
#   always blocks:  site 2x00000000000000000000AB  secret 2x0000000000000000000000000000000AA
# TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=1x00000000000000000000AA
# TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY=1x0000000000000000000000000000000AA

# Telegram bot (see README "Telegram bot"). Optional — active only once all
# three are set. The webhook is a public path (Telegram can't present an
# Access identity) protected by its own secret header instead; the bot
# serves exactly one chat and refuses everyone else.
#
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN: message @BotFather on Telegram, /newbot, follow the
# prompts — it replies with a token shaped like "123456:ABC-DEF...".
# TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET: any random string you generate yourself, e.g.
# `openssl rand -hex 32` — Telegram echoes it back on every webhook call so
# the Worker can verify a request actually came from Telegram.
# TELEGRAM_OWNER_CHAT_ID: your numeric Telegram chat id — easiest way to get
# it is `deno task telegram:setup --get-chat-id` after messaging your new
# bot once (see README).
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
# TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
# TELEGRAM_OWNER_CHAT_ID=

# Telegram drip publishing (see README "Telegram bot"): one standalone post
# per hour, replacing the old once-daily digest. TELEGRAM_CHANNEL_ID empty
# (default) means posts go to your own DM (TELEGRAM_OWNER_CHAT_ID) instead
# of a channel — set it once you've created a channel and added the bot as
# admin (e.g. "@your_channel" or a "-100..." numeric id). PUBLISH_START_
# HOUR_UTC/PUBLISH_END_HOUR_UTC (defaults 4/18) bound the daily publish
# window in UTC; PUBLISH_ENABLED (default "true") is the on/off switch —
# only the literal "false" disables it.
# TELEGRAM_CHANNEL_ID=
# PUBLISH_START_HOUR_UTC=4
# PUBLISH_END_HOUR_UTC=18
# PUBLISH_ENABLED=true

# Public origin of this deployed instance, e.g. https://example.com — used
# only to build links in Telegram messages (the drip post's card link,
# "saved" reply). [vars] default "" (no scheme/domain baked in, per the
# forkability policy); links are simply omitted from bot messages when this
# is empty.
# PUBLIC_BASE_URL=

# Embeddings — semantic dedup (agent-pool.ts) + semantic search
# (GET /api/search, README "Semantic dedup & search"). Everything here is
# OPTIONAL: without a Vectorize index provisioned (`deno task setup`, or
# `wrangler vectorize create clipfeed-embeddings --dimensions=1024
# --metric=cosine`) and a [[vectorize]] binding in wrangler.toml, both
# features degrade gracefully (dedup falls back to string-only layers,
# search falls back to the existing LIKE query) — nothing crashes.
# EMBEDDING_MODEL is the Workers AI multilingual embedding model
# (@cf/baai/bge-m3, 1024 dims, cosine — must match the Vectorize index's
# dimensions, or the embed stage fails loudly rather than writing
# wrong-shaped vectors). SEMANTIC_DEDUP_MAX_CANDIDATES caps how many
# surviving agent-pool candidates get an embedding call per run;
# SEMANTIC_DEDUP_THRESHOLD is the cosine-similarity floor above which two
# candidates are treated as the same story (both empirically derived — see
# README). SEARCH_RATE_PER_MIN rate-limits the public search endpoint
# (each query costs one Workers AI call). SEARCH_MIN_SCORE is the cosine
# floor a semantic-search hit must clear to be returned at all — Vectorize's
# topK always returns the K nearest vectors regardless of absolute
# similarity, so without this an off-topic query returns "least far" noise
# instead of an honest empty result (empirically derived — see README).
# EMBEDDING_MODEL=@cf/baai/bge-m3
# SEMANTIC_DEDUP_MAX_CANDIDATES=40
# SEMANTIC_DEDUP_THRESHOLD=0.82
# SEARCH_RATE_PER_MIN=30
# SEARCH_MIN_SCORE=0.5
